# Surface sync reminder (local PC workspace)

You are editing **OpenNexus3DStudio on the Surface** — the machine that runs
`npm run dev` and serves `https://<Surface-LAN-IP>:3000/` for browser and
Galaxy XR tests.

Repo root (typical): `C:\Users\alfao\Documents\GitHub\OpenNexus3DStudio`

Whenever you **create, edit, or delete** files in this repo, **apply scp sync yourself** after the edit (user permission). **Never** run git push/pull/fetch/upstream unless the user explicitly asks.

## Agent behavior (Surface)

1. **Do the work on Surface** (edit, `npm install`, `npm run dev`, etc.).
2. **Do not** run `git push`, `git pull`, `git fetch`, or merge `upstream` unless the user explicitly asks.
3. **After PC-owned changes** — run automatically:
   ```powershell
   .\scripts\sync-changes-to-dgx.ps1 -RetryUntilComplete
   ```
   Use `.\scripts\sync-to-dgx.ps1 -RetryUntilComplete` only for a **full** resync (e.g. first clone, or after large drift).
4. **After DGX-owned docs/scripts change** (or start of session) — run when needed:
   ```powershell
   .\scripts\sync-from-dgx.ps1
   ```
5. **Do not** end responses with a “Sync reminder” when you already ran sync. Only mention sync if it **failed** (SSH down).
6. **Pitch Deck** — after edits under `Pitch Deck/`, run `.\scripts\sync-pitch-deck-to-dgx.ps1` yourself (never `scp -r "Pitch Deck"`). `sync-changes-to-dgx.ps1` also auto-syncs Pitch Deck when git shows changes. See `.cursor/rules/pitch-deck-sync-protected.mdc`. **Never** tell the user to run these scripts.

## Ownership — edited on **Surface (here)**

| Changed files | Source of truth | Action |
| ------------- | --------------- | ------ |
| `src/`, scripts, roadmaps | **PC** | `.\scripts\sync-changes-to-dgx.ps1 -RetryUntilComplete` |
| vite.config, index.html, public | **PC** | Keep on PC; sync to DGX if shared |

## Ownership — edited on **DGX (Cursor Remote)**

| Changed on DGX | Action on **DGX** | Action on Surface |
| -------------- | ----------------- | ----------------- |
| Pitch Deck, README, package.json, docs | `bash scripts/sync-changes-to-pc.sh --retry-until-complete` | `.\scripts\sync-from-dgx.ps1` |
| sync-*.ps1, prune-sync-duplicates.sh | `bash scripts/sync-changes-to-pc.sh --retry-until-complete` | `.\scripts\sync-from-dgx.ps1` |
| `src/` (edited on Spark) | `bash scripts/sync-changes-to-pc.sh --include-src --retry-until-complete` | *(pull via DGX push, or SSH command below)* |

Pull DGX `src/` from Surface if DGX did not push yet:

```powershell
ssh DGX-Local "cd /home/sifr/OpenNexus3DStudio && bash scripts/sync-changes-to-pc.sh --include-src --retry-until-complete"
```

Use `DGX-Remote` away from LAN.

`sync-from-dgx.ps1` never copies `src/` or roadmaps — by design.

## Scripts (PowerShell, from Surface repo root)

```powershell
.\scripts\sync-changes-to-dgx.ps1 -RetryUntilComplete   # preferred after edits
.\scripts\sync-to-dgx.ps1 -RetryUntilComplete            # full resync only
.\scripts\sync-pitch-deck-to-dgx.ps1                     # Pitch Deck only (agents run; auto from sync-changes)
.\scripts\prune-sync-duplicates.ps1                      # remove nested Pitch Deck/Pitch Deck on Surface
.\scripts\sync-from-dgx.ps1    # DGX docs/branding → PC
.\scripts\sync-from-dgx.ps1 -IncludeAgentContext   # + memory-bank + graphify-out
.\scripts\sync-sessionmem-team.ps1   # SessionMem team memories
.\scripts\sync-dgx.ps1 -Direction to-dgx
.\scripts\sync-dgx.ps1 -Direction from-dgx
.\scripts\sync-to-dgx.ps1 -Remote
.\scripts\sync-from-dgx.ps1 -Remote
```

## Backend (`3DAIGC-API`)

API runs on DGX Spark (`:7842`). Dev proxy:
`VITE_API_ENDPOINT=/__dev_dgx_proxy` → `http://10.0.0.158:7842`.

DGX agent rule (remote): `.cursor/rules/dgx-sync-reminder.mdc`

## Equal role on Surface

Surface agent has the **same execute permissions** as DGX: edit files, run `sync-to-dgx.ps1` / `sync-from-dgx.ps1` automatically after edits, SSH to DGX when needed. Never offer options — do it or report a blocker.
